<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-09-02T04:35:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-09-02T04:35:00-05:00" n="433" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d433">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00115 European War 1939/1371:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Dreyfus</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-09-02T13:00:00+03:25">September 2, 1941—1
                                        p.m.</date><lb/>[Received September 3—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>132. The Turkish Chargé d’Affaires informs me he received this
                                morning new instructions from his Government authorizing him to
                                grant refuge to Germans only in occupied parts of Iran. This would
                                preclude the granting of asylum to Germans here and avoid the
                                complication mentioned in my number 130.<note n="23" xml:id="d433fn23"><hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi></note></p>
                            <p>This relieves a situation which was being viewed most seriously by
                                the Iranian Government and the British Legation replies to
                                Ankara.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Dreyfus</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>